## Global Risk Changes

- Academy and Mining advance from older candidate/D2 snapshots to accepted L4 Consolidated/D3+ non-production closure states; execution-sensitive risks are unchanged.
- Defi advances from the older readiness snapshot to `L4_CONSOLIDATED_NON_PRODUCTION`; D-Level remains unassessed and critical blockers remain open.
- ACS closure is a pause/handoff, not L4 Consolidated promotion.
- Marketplace remains backlog-ready, not the immediate priority.
- Documentation publication authority and versioning are the preferred control gap to resolve.

## Blockers Preserved

Globally blocked: production, treasury execution, custody, wallet/signing, financial execution, provider execution, contract writes, real yield, settlement, payouts, billing execution, real credentials, production APIs, production databases, regulated product readiness and investment recommendation.

Academy certification/rewards/minting, Mining real mining/hashrate/equipment/capital allocation, Defi financial and admin mutation surfaces, Trading live exchange activity, Lottery randomness/prizes/compliance, Marketplace settlement, and ACS provisioning/runtime mutation also remain blocked.

